OISTAT â€“ International Organisation of Scenographers, Theatre Architects and Technicians is a non-governmental organization (NGO) founded 1968 in Prague, Czech Republic. According to its founding name, the organization is mainly a network for theatre designers, theatre architects and theatre technicians around the world. It is made up people associated with creating or studies on live performances, including educators, researchers and practitioners. The organization has members from around the world, currently in 53 countries with membership categories: Centre Member, Associate Member and Individual Member.
